        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 4 at 7:08PM EDT until September 4 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBGM

The National Weather Service in Binghamton has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Luzerne County in northeastern Pennsylvania...

* Until 800 PM EDT.

* At 708 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Mifflinville,
or near Berwick, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Muhlenberg, Berwick, Nanticoke, Nescopeck, Slocum, Shickshinny,
Nuangola, New Columbus, East Berwick, and Pond Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with this storm. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is
one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder,
you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
